description: PUH-BrianMartell The -1/12 result (Ramanujan summation of 1+2+3+…) is the Standard Model’s most famous “accounting trick” — it lets them subtract infinities to get finite answers (Casimir effect, critical string dimensions). But it’s a patch for assuming continuous space with infinite modes. PUH v25 eliminates the need: The E8 photonic lattice is discrete — finite units (240 roots projected), natural cutoff at Master Unit scale. No infinite sum → no infinity → no renormalization required. Derivation: •  Standard: Vacuum energy sum modes k → ∞ diverges → ζ(-1) = -1/12 “regularizes” to finite. •  PUH: Modes finite N_E8 ~240 projected + compact internal — sum \sum n = N(N+1)/2 large positive finite, no negative ghost. •  Casimir: Plates restrict lattice modes → pressure difference mechanical substrate exclusion, positive finite no -1/12 needed.
